  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What should I gift to my teacher?",
  "response": "Choosing a thoughtful gift for your teacher can be a wonderful way to show your appreciation. Here are several ideas across different price ranges:\n\n1. **Handwritten Note or Card**: A heartfelt message expressing your gratitude and highlighting how they have positively impacted your life can be very meaningful.\n\n2. **Gift Cards**: Opt for a gift card to a bookstore, coffee shop, or office supply store. This allows them to choose something they truly want or need.\n\n3. **Personalized Items**: Consider items like a customized mug, tote bag, or desk accessory with their name or a special message.\n\n4. **Classroom Supplies**: Teachers often spend their own money on classroom supplies. Items like colorful markers, notebooks, or decorative materials can be very useful.\n\n5. **A Potted Plant**: A small succulent or indoor plant can brighten up their desk and is relatively easy to maintain.\n\n6. **Books**: If you know their taste in books, a good read could be a great gift. Alternatively, consider a book on a subject they teach or a popular new release.\n\n7. **Homemade Treats**: Baking some cookies or other homemade goods can add a personal touch to your gift.\n\n8. **Subscription Services**: A subscription to a magazine they enjoy or a streaming service could be a delightful surprise.\n\n9. **A Nice Pen or Notebook**: High-quality stationery can be both practical and appreciated for personal or professional use.\n\n10. **Relaxation Gifts**: A small set with items like a candle, bath soak, or tea can encourage them to unwind.\n\nRemember, the thoughtfulness and sincerity behind your gift are what truly count. Consider the teacher\u2019s personality and preferences when making your choice.",
